INSERT INTO `entries` VALUES (7,1,'introduction-to-google-s-android-platform','Introduction to Google\'s Android Platform','<p>As the title says Android is a platform that include operation system,middleware and also application programming interface(api) which is create by Google.It is a solution for developers to create rich mobile applications easily with the power and easiness of Java programming language .Why it is a solution cause mobile systems like symbian and java midlets didnt gave so much flexibility that Android platform gave to developers.  By using Symbian platform you can write applications that access the hardware of the device but it require so much complex c/c++ code.This is kind of tiresome for developers using symbian platform.After symbian platform <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Java_Platform,_Micro_Edition\">Java MIDlets</a> have evolved and MIDlets fix the difficult hardware access in mobile platforms by abstracting the underlying hardware platform and giving developers ability to create applications that run on wide variety of platforms that support java run time.Cost of this platform independence is restricted access to hardware.Cause native and third party application doesnt have the same priority.Third party application recieve restricted access to hardware platform.This cant be good for the third party application especially developers who create application for that platform</p>\r\n<p><strong><h3>What makes Google Android Different?</h3></strong></p>\r\n<p>Developers can use Java to create applications for the Android platform.This is a big advantage cause Java accepted by developers all over the world and has great support&nbsp; and most important it is open source like Android platform itself.But what known wrong here that you can not use Java classes directly and write application for the Android platform you have to make your classes and strcutre of your application specific to Android platform.  Antoher difference is that all applications at Android platform whether its a native application or third party they have the same priority.This gives huge flexibility to third party applications , as other platforms do opposite.They gave restricted access to third party application and also restricted resource.  Android platform built on linux kernel and it is a open source platform.You can even write low level code for platform.Also Android is a member of Open Mobile Alliance and Linux Phone Standarts Forum(LiPS).There is&nbsp; wrong belief that&nbsp; Android platform is fully open source, well it is not true right now but it is expected to be fully open source.</p>\r\n<blockquote>At this stage, not all of the Android stack has been released as open source, although this is expected to happen by the time phones are released to market. It&rsquo;s also worth noting that the applications you develop for Android do not have to be open source.</blockquote>\r\n<p>And also your application doesnt have to be open source , you can make money from it, it is a developers choice to make it open source or not.There is a&nbsp; market that has the same functionality like Apple\'s app strore named Android market.You can look at android applications from <a href=\"http://www.google.com.tr/url?sa=t&amp;source=web&amp;ct=res&amp;cd=1&amp;ved=0CAsQFjAA&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.android.com%2Fmarket%2F&amp;rct=j&amp;q=android+market&amp;ei=k07jSqK1M8eJsAbfguSCAw&amp;usg=AFQjCNHgu7PtEG-1FSR868o4WLQnIsxAPg&amp;sig2=v0wwVBw0LcyE2ipc6hNlDw\">Android Market</a>.  As a general belief it is not a competitor to Apples Ä°phone.Cause iphone is fully hardware and software platform but Android only offers a general software stack that can run on every hardware platform that meet Android requirements.Unlike Apple\'s iphone there is not one Android Mobile Phone.You can check latest Android supported mobile phones <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Android_%28operating_system%29\">here</a>.  Android also has a rich <a href=\"http://developer.android.com/reference/packages.html\">api</a> and <a href=\"http://developer.android.com/guide/index.html\">great documentation</a>.Also you can download latest SDK from <a href=\"http://developer.android.com/sdk/1.6_r1/index.html\">here</a>.What makes Android so attractive is that its open philosophy,you can create or even change applications like you imagine them.</p>','<p>As the title says Android is a platform that include operation system,middleware and also application programming interface(api) which is create by Google.It is a solution for developers to create rich mobile applications easily with the power and easiness of Java programming language .Why it is a solution cause mobile systems like symbian and java midlets didnt gave so much flexibility that Android platform gave to developers.  By using Symbian platform you can write applications that access the hardware of the device but it require so much complex c/c++ code.This is kind of tiresome for developers using symbian platform.After symbian platform <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Java_Platform,_Micro_Edition\">Java MIDlets</a> have evolved and MIDlets fix the difficult hardware access in mobile platforms by abstracting the underlying hardware platform and giving developers ability to create applications that run on wide variety of platforms that support java run time.Cost of this platform independence is restricted access to hardware.Cause native and third party application doesnt have the same priority.Third party application recieve restricted access to hardware platform.This cant be good for the third party application especially developers who create application for that platform</p>\n\n<p><strong><h3>What makes Google Android Different?</h3></strong></p>\n\n<p>Developers can use Java to create applications for the Android platform.This is a big advantage cause Java accepted by developers all over the world and has great support&nbsp; and most important it is open source like Android platform itself.But what known wrong here that you can not use Java classes directly and write application for the Android platform you have to make your classes and strcutre of your application specific to Android platform.  Antoher difference is that all applications at Android platform whether its a native application or third party they have the same priority.This gives huge flexibility to third party applications , as other platforms do opposite.They gave restricted access to third party application and also restricted resource.  Android platform built on linux kernel and it is a open source platform.You can even write low level code for platform.Also Android is a member of Open Mobile Alliance and Linux Phone Standarts Forum(LiPS).There is&nbsp; wrong belief that&nbsp; Android platform is fully open source, well it is not true right now but it is expected to be fully open source.</p>\n\n<blockquote>At this stage, not all of the Android stack has been released as open source, although this is expected to happen by the time phones are released to market. It&rsquo;s also worth noting that the applications you develop for Android do not have to be open source.</blockquote>\n\n<p>And also your application doesnt have to be open source , you can make money from it, it is a developers choice to make it open source or not.There is a&nbsp; market that has the same functionality like Apple\'s app strore named Android market.You can look at android applications from <a href=\"http://www.google.com.tr/url?sa=t&amp;source=web&amp;ct=res&amp;cd=1&amp;ved=0CAsQFjAA&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.android.com%2Fmarket%2F&amp;rct=j&amp;q=android+market&amp;ei=k07jSqK1M8eJsAbfguSCAw&amp;usg=AFQjCNHgu7PtEG-1FSR868o4WLQnIsxAPg&amp;sig2=v0wwVBw0LcyE2ipc6hNlDw\">Android Market</a>.  As a general belief it is not a competitor to Apples Ä°phone.Cause iphone is fully hardware and software platform but Android only offers a general software stack that can run on every hardware platform that meet Android requirements.Unlike Apple\'s iphone there is not one Android Mobile Phone.You can check latest Android supported mobile phones <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Android_%28operating_system%29\">here</a>.  Android also has a rich <a href=\"http://developer.android.com/reference/packages.html\">api</a> and <a href=\"http://developer.android.com/guide/index.html\">great documentation</a>.Also you can download latest SDK from <a href=\"http://developer.android.com/sdk/1.6_r1/index.html\">here</a>.What makes Android so attractive is that its open philosophy,you can create or even change applications like you imagine them.</p>','2011-10-05 23:21:43','2011-10-05 23:21:43'),(8,1,'auto-boxing-and-unboxing-with-java-generics','(Auto)Boxing and Unboxing with Java Generics','<p>As you may know auto boxing and unboxing is a new feature of the Java 6.(which is not new for languages like C#, we can say it is new feature for the Java).Java has two main data types one is primitive type and other is reference types.Primitive types are the types generally built in language (like int , short,byte,long,float,double,bool,char...) and allocated on the stack side of the memory.But reference types are the types lets say shortly any type that subtype of the class Object in java (like class,array,String...) and they allocated on the heap side of the memory.  What about boxing and unboxing , boxing is conversion of the one primitive type to its corresponding reference type (int to Integer in this situation) while unboxing is conversion of the reference type to corresponding primitive type.You can think of actually \"boxing\" the varaible and putting it to heap side , and unboxing as reverse procedure to the stack side.  These boxing and unboxing operations are automatically done by java while using generics.Generics&nbsp; can think of as a compile time check for class or interface or any other types that used with generics for their parameters.From definition its hard to understand so lets show a example of generics use.</p>\r\n<pre lang=\"java\">List&lt;Integer&gt; ints = new ArrayList&lt;Integer&gt;();\r\nints.add(1);\r\nint n = ints.get(0);</pre>\r\n<p>Here as you can see we are creating a list from arraylist(which is a class the implements list interface so assigment is OK) with specified parameters String in angle brackets.With the help of generics it is guaranteed that all the parameters that added to arraylist is String , if you try to add something other that String it is a compile time error.Before java generics its programmer job to guess what is the variable type coming from list and make suitable cast to that object.It is a extra work for programmer.With generics its is now compiler responsibility to check parameters and give compile time error.  You can say it is not different from c++ templates , but actually it does.There is a different implementation of the generics in bot c++ and java side.In C++ if you use generics and create and objects lets say List&lt;String&gt; and List&lt;Integer&gt; and List&lt;List&lt;String&gt;&gt; , C++ made 3 copy of your code for each generic in use.If you use 100 different type of generics there will be 100 different code , this can lead to code bloat.But in java no matter how many differnt generics you use there is only one code for all.C++ model generics called expansion,it can be lead to code bloat but in performance side it is more efficient that Java model.Also if you are using generics with C++ you have to be careful about usage of angle brackets.  Lets look at another code to see how auto boxing and unboxing work with Java.</p>\r\n<pre lang=\"java\">public static int sum (List&lt;Integer&gt; ints) {\r\n  int s = 0;\r\n  for (int n : ints) { s += n; }\r\n  return s;\r\n}</pre>\r\n<p>In this code sample we again using a list from arraylist as&nbsp; parameter to sum function with specified Integer generic.(you can say what is the difference between \"Integer\" and \"int\" , and why we not using \"int\" for generics like this \"List&lt;int&gt; ints\") Cause type parameters always bound to reference type not primitive types.And also you can ask why we are using \"int\" insted of \"Integer\" as return type like \"return Integer\"? .Because result types may be either primitive or reference types, and it is more  efficient to use the former than the latter.Also you can say why for variable(or you can say foreach another new feature of java 6) not \"Integer\" insted of&nbsp; \"int\".This is actually hold performace issue behind.If you use \"Integer\" instead of \"int\" compiler unbox the value of \"Integer\" every time and perform operation than box the value back for later iteration.This is a big performance loss.  Here how generics doing auto boxing and unboxing.</p>\r\n<pre lang=\"java\">List&lt;Integer&gt; ints = new ArrayList&lt;Integer&gt;();\r\nints.add(new Integer(1));\r\nint n = ints.get(0).intValue();</pre>\r\n<p>This is the different version of the first code sample at top.This is how it looks when we are using generics in our code.As you can see if we try to add int value to List that expects Integer , it automatically box the value and then add it to the list.On the other hand if we try to get the value out of list , it again automatically unbox the value and assign it .(here we using integer so if we try to box int value it is done with new Integer(x) , and if we try to unbox it you have to call intValue method of the Integer).  For more information about generics you can look at Sun documentation for <a href=\"http://java.sun.com/docs/books/tutorial/java/generics/index.html\">generics </a>and also for <a href=\"http://java.sun.com/docs/books/tutorial/collections/index.html\">Collections framework</a> of Java.</p>','<p>As you may know auto boxing and unboxing is a new feature of the Java 6.(which is not new for languages like C#, we can say it is new feature for the Java).Java has two main data types one is primitive type and other is reference types.Primitive types are the types generally built in language (like int , short,byte,long,float,double,bool,char...) and allocated on the stack side of the memory.But reference types are the types lets say shortly any type that subtype of the class Object in java (like class,array,String...) and they allocated on the heap side of the memory.  What about boxing and unboxing , boxing is conversion of the one primitive type to its corresponding reference type (int to Integer in this situation) while unboxing is conversion of the reference type to corresponding primitive type.You can think of actually \"boxing\" the varaible and putting it to heap side , and unboxing as reverse procedure to the stack side.  These boxing and unboxing operations are automatically done by java while using generics.Generics&nbsp; can think of as a compile time check for class or interface or any other types that used with generics for their parameters.From definition its hard to understand so lets show a example of generics use.</p>\n\n<pre lang=\"java\">List&lt;Integer&gt; ints = new ArrayList&lt;Integer&gt;();\nints.add(1);\nint n = ints.get(0);</pre>\n\n<p>Here as you can see we are creating a list from arraylist(which is a class the implements list interface so assigment is OK) with specified parameters String in angle brackets.With the help of generics it is guaranteed that all the parameters that added to arraylist is String , if you try to add something other that String it is a compile time error.Before java generics its programmer job to guess what is the variable type coming from list and make suitable cast to that object.It is a extra work for programmer.With generics its is now compiler responsibility to check parameters and give compile time error.  You can say it is not different from c++ templates , but actually it does.There is a different implementation of the generics in bot c++ and java side.In C++ if you use generics and create and objects lets say List&lt;String&gt; and List&lt;Integer&gt; and List&lt;List&lt;String&gt;&gt; , C++ made 3 copy of your code for each generic in use.If you use 100 different type of generics there will be 100 different code , this can lead to code bloat.But in java no matter how many differnt generics you use there is only one code for all.C++ model generics called expansion,it can be lead to code bloat but in performance side it is more efficient that Java model.Also if you are using generics with C++ you have to be careful about usage of angle brackets.  Lets look at another code to see how auto boxing and unboxing work with Java.</p>\n\n<pre lang=\"java\">public static int sum (List&lt;Integer&gt; ints) {\n  int s = 0;\n  for (int n : ints) { s += n; }\n  return s;\n}</pre>\n\n<p>In this code sample we again using a list from arraylist as&nbsp; parameter to sum function with specified Integer generic.(you can say what is the difference between \"Integer\" and \"int\" , and why we not using \"int\" for generics like this \"List&lt;int&gt; ints\") Cause type parameters always bound to reference type not primitive types.And also you can ask why we are using \"int\" insted of \"Integer\" as return type like \"return Integer\"? .Because result types may be either primitive or reference types, and it is more  efficient to use the former than the latter.Also you can say why for variable(or you can say foreach another new feature of java 6) not \"Integer\" insted of&nbsp; \"int\".This is actually hold performace issue behind.If you use \"Integer\" instead of \"int\" compiler unbox the value of \"Integer\" every time and perform operation than box the value back for later iteration.This is a big performance loss.  Here how generics doing auto boxing and unboxing.</p>\n\n<pre lang=\"java\">List&lt;Integer&gt; ints = new ArrayList&lt;Integer&gt;();\nints.add(new Integer(1));\nint n = ints.get(0).intValue();</pre>\n\n<p>This is the different version of the first code sample at top.This is how it looks when we are using generics in our code.As you can see if we try to add int value to List that expects Integer , it automatically box the value and then add it to the list.On the other hand if we try to get the value out of list , it again automatically unbox the value and assign it .(here we using integer so if we try to box int value it is done with new Integer(x) , and if we try to unbox it you have to call intValue method of the Integer).  For more information about generics you can look at Sun documentation for <a href=\"http://java.sun.com/docs/books/tutorial/java/generics/index.html\">generics </a>and also for <a href=\"http://java.sun.com/docs/books/tutorial/collections/index.html\">Collections framework</a> of Java.</p>','2011-10-05 23:23:09','2011-10-05 23:23:09'),(9,1,'introduction-to-j2me-platform','Introduction To J2ME Platform','<p>J2ME isn&rsquo;t a specific piece of software or specification. All it means is Java for small devices. Small devices range in size from pagers, mobile phones, and personal digital assistants (PDAs) all the way up to things like set-top boxes.  J2ME is divided into <strong>configurations, profiles, and optional APIs</strong>, which provide specific information about APIs and different families of devices. A configuration is designed for a specific kind of device based on memory constraints and processor power. It specifies a Java Virtual Machine (JVM) that can be easily ported to devices supporting the configuration. It also specifies a strict subset of the <strong>Java 2 Platform, Standard Edition (J2SE) API</strong>s that will be used on the platform, as well as additional APIs that may be necessary. Device manufacturers are responsible for porting a specific configuration to their devices.</p>\r\n<p><h3>What is profiles?</h3></p>\r\n<p>Profiles are more specific than configurations. A profile is based on a configuration and provides additional APIs, such as user interface, persistent storage, and whatever else is necessary to develop running applications for the device.  Optional APIs define specific additional functionality that may be included in a particular configuration (or profile). The whole caboodle&mdash;configuration, profile, and optional APIs&mdash; that is implemented on a device is called a stack. For example, a possible future device stack might be CLDC/MIDP + Mobile Media API. See the section &ldquo;Platform Standardization&rdquo; later in this chapter for information on JSR 185, which defines a standard J2ME stack.  J2ME configuration divided into 2 categories according to device specifications.First one is <strong>Connected Device Configuration</strong> called CDC which sits on top of the J2ME.These devices have to meet the requirements specified by JSR community process.CDC devices target especially high end PDA\'s , navigation systems , settop boxes.Therse devices has ,at a minimum, 512KB of read-only memory (ROM), 256KB of random access memory (RAM), and some kind of network connection.And also CDC devices gives full JVM support.  Other type of configuration is <strong>Connected Limited Device Configuration</strong> which is called CLDC.This configuration category include devices like mobile phones,pagers,PDA\'s...As you see these devices smaller than the devices listed on CDC.CDC devices have limited memory , limited processor power ,limited screen size,limited battery life because of these developing applications for these devices is a important process.The CLDC is designed for devices with 160KB to 512KB of total memory, including a minimum of 160KB of ROM and 32KB of RAM available for the Java platform.For note connected means here network connection that is not very fast and intermitted.These devices support specific implementation of JVM which is KVM.K means here as far as i know \"it is a JVM whose size is measured in kilobytes rather than megabytes\".  Other important part of J2ME is profiles.I am not going to dive into other profiles just MIDP which is the important and known one &nbsp;in J2ME development.MIDP stands for Mobile Information Device Profile and have also JSR process and specifications.Here is the MIDP 2.0 specifications.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>A minimum of 256KB of ROM for the MIDP implementation (this is in addition to the requirements of the CLDC)</li>\r\n<li>A minimum of 128KB of RAM for the Java runtime heap</li>\r\n<li> A minimum of 8KB of nonvolatile writable memory for persistent data</li>\r\n<li> A screen of at least 96&times;54 pixels &bull;	Some capacity for input, either by keypad, keyboard, or touch screen</li>\r\n<li> Two-way network connection, possibly intermittent</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><em>Most of the latest devices support MIDP 2.0 specification but older ones user MIDP 1.0.</em> <strong>Structure of MIDP Application</strong> <strong> </strong>MIDP application has a API which comes from both CLDC and also MIDP 2.0 .CLCD api comes from core api defined in Java SE and MIDP api comes with java micro edition packages.Here is a list of avaliable packages.  For CLDC</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>java.lang</li>\r\n<li>java.lang.ref</li>\r\n<li>java.io</li>\r\n<li>java.util</li>\r\n<li>javax.microedition.io</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>For MIDP</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>javax.microedition.lcdui</li>\r\n<li>javax.microedition.lcdui.game</li>\r\n<li>javax.microedition.media</li>\r\n<li>javax.microedition.media.control</li>\r\n<li>javax.microedition.midlet</li>\r\n<li>javax.microedition.pki</li>\r\n<li>javax.microedition.rms</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Also device vendors supply their own API\'s specific to their device.These are different API\'s from MIDP and as i said specific to that device not platform independent and make developers to reach device specific features.MIDP applications sits on top of the device specific OS , and use only api provided by MIDP and CLDC.Device specific java application use API provided by device vendor.(Device Specific API\'s).  <strong>Advantages of MIDP</strong> Portability  The advantage of using Java over using other tools for small device application development is portability. You could write device applications with C or C++, but the result would be specific to a single platform. An application written using the MIDP APIs will be directly portable to any MIDP device.  Security  A second compelling reason for using Java for small device development is security. Java is well known for its ability to safely run downloaded code like applets. This is a perfect fit&mdash;it&rsquo;s easy to imagine nifty applications dynamically downloading to your mobile phone.</p>','<p>J2ME isn&rsquo;t a specific piece of software or specification. All it means is Java for small devices. Small devices range in size from pagers, mobile phones, and personal digital assistants (PDAs) all the way up to things like set-top boxes.  J2ME is divided into <strong>configurations, profiles, and optional APIs</strong>, which provide specific information about APIs and different families of devices. A configuration is designed for a specific kind of device based on memory constraints and processor power. It specifies a Java Virtual Machine (JVM) that can be easily ported to devices supporting the configuration. It also specifies a strict subset of the <strong>Java 2 Platform, Standard Edition (J2SE) API</strong>s that will be used on the platform, as well as additional APIs that may be necessary. Device manufacturers are responsible for porting a specific configuration to their devices.</p>\n\n<p><h3>What is profiles?</h3></p>\n\n<p>Profiles are more specific than configurations. A profile is based on a configuration and provides additional APIs, such as user interface, persistent storage, and whatever else is necessary to develop running applications for the device.  Optional APIs define specific additional functionality that may be included in a particular configuration (or profile). The whole caboodle&mdash;configuration, profile, and optional APIs&mdash; that is implemented on a device is called a stack. For example, a possible future device stack might be CLDC/MIDP + Mobile Media API. See the section &ldquo;Platform Standardization&rdquo; later in this chapter for information on JSR 185, which defines a standard J2ME stack.  J2ME configuration divided into 2 categories according to device specifications.First one is <strong>Connected Device Configuration</strong> called CDC which sits on top of the J2ME.These devices have to meet the requirements specified by JSR community process.CDC devices target especially high end PDA\'s , navigation systems , settop boxes.Therse devices has ,at a minimum, 512KB of read-only memory (ROM), 256KB of random access memory (RAM), and some kind of network connection.And also CDC devices gives full JVM support.  Other type of configuration is <strong>Connected Limited Device Configuration</strong> which is called CLDC.This configuration category include devices like mobile phones,pagers,PDA\'s...As you see these devices smaller than the devices listed on CDC.CDC devices have limited memory , limited processor power ,limited screen size,limited battery life because of these developing applications for these devices is a important process.The CLDC is designed for devices with 160KB to 512KB of total memory, including a minimum of 160KB of ROM and 32KB of RAM available for the Java platform.For note connected means here network connection that is not very fast and intermitted.These devices support specific implementation of JVM which is KVM.K means here as far as i know \"it is a JVM whose size is measured in kilobytes rather than megabytes\".  Other important part of J2ME is profiles.I am not going to dive into other profiles just MIDP which is the important and known one &nbsp;in J2ME development.MIDP stands for Mobile Information Device Profile and have also JSR process and specifications.Here is the MIDP 2.0 specifications.</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>A minimum of 256KB of ROM for the MIDP implementation (this is in addition to the requirements of the CLDC)</li>\n<li>A minimum of 128KB of RAM for the Java runtime heap</li>\n<li> A minimum of 8KB of nonvolatile writable memory for persistent data</li>\n<li> A screen of at least 96&times;54 pixels &bull; Some capacity for input, either by keypad, keyboard, or touch screen</li>\n<li> Two-way network connection, possibly intermittent</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><em>Most of the latest devices support MIDP 2.0 specification but older ones user MIDP 1.0.</em> <strong>Structure of MIDP Application</strong> <strong> </strong>MIDP application has a API which comes from both CLDC and also MIDP 2.0 .CLCD api comes from core api defined in Java SE and MIDP api comes with java micro edition packages.Here is a list of avaliable packages.  For CLDC</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>java.lang</li>\n<li>java.lang.ref</li>\n<li>java.io</li>\n<li>java.util</li>\n<li>javax.microedition.io</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>For MIDP</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>javax.microedition.lcdui</li>\n<li>javax.microedition.lcdui.game</li>\n<li>javax.microedition.media</li>\n<li>javax.microedition.media.control</li>\n<li>javax.microedition.midlet</li>\n<li>javax.microedition.pki</li>\n<li>javax.microedition.rms</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Also device vendors supply their own API\'s specific to their device.These are different API\'s from MIDP and as i said specific to that device not platform independent and make developers to reach device specific features.MIDP applications sits on top of the device specific OS , and use only api provided by MIDP and CLDC.Device specific java application use API provided by device vendor.(Device Specific API\'s).  <strong>Advantages of MIDP</strong> Portability  The advantage of using Java over using other tools for small device application development is portability. You could write device applications with C or C++, but the result would be specific to a single platform. An application written using the MIDP APIs will be directly portable to any MIDP device.  Security  A second compelling reason for using Java for small device development is security. Java is well known for its ability to safely run downloaded code like applets. This is a perfect fit&mdash;it&rsquo;s easy to imagine nifty applications dynamically downloading to your mobile phone.</p>','2011-10-05 23:26:08','2011-10-05 23:26:08'),(10,1,'java-quirk-label-plus-line-comment','Java Quirk | Label plus Line Comment','<p>Last day while writing some java code sample i accidently paste and http link into main method , normally this must give me error from compiler but it didnt gave any error , than i realize whats going on</p>\r\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270004.js?file=StrangeJava\"></script>\r\n<p>The trick here is that http: means that programmer defining a new label that jump the program execution to that label and two slashed follow as you may know one line comment . Java has no goto keyword thats right but you can implement similar approach with labels.Lets look at the code for example...</p>\r\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270009.js?file=StrangeJava2\"></script>','<p>Last day while writing some java code sample i accidently paste and http link into main method , normally this must give me error from compiler but it didnt gave any error , than i realize whats going on</p>\n\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270004.js?file=StrangeJava\"></script>\n\n<p>The trick here is that http: means that programmer defining a new label that jump the program execution to that label and two slashed follow as you may know one line comment . Java has no goto keyword thats right but you can implement similar approach with labels.Lets look at the code for example...</p>\n\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270009.js?file=StrangeJava2\"></script>','2011-10-05 23:27:50','2011-10-07 10:43:29'),(11,1,'java-quirk-hello-world-without-main-method','Java Quirk | Hello World without Main Method','<p>If you are java programmer or reading lots of books about java , you always see something in first chapters that there must be at least one main method for a java application to run or at least jvm know where to start to run the application. Here is a little java hack that prints the hello world string without using main method instead using static initialization block and than print the string to the console , try to run from command line cause eclipse would not allow you to run the application cause it doesnt hava main method.\r\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1269997.js?file=static_main\"></script>\r\n<p>Probably after running and loading the class you get an error saying that i can not find the main method to run, you can bypass this error by providing System.exit(0) to inform the compiler , on background System.exit is calling</p>\r\n<blockquote>Runtime.getRuntime().exit(n)</blockquote>\r\n<p>and than it should work and succesfully run the application.</p>\r\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1269998.js?file=static_main2\"></script>\r\n<p>You should check static <a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/javaOO/initial.html\">initialization</a> if you are wondering the answer and also look at <a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/javase/1.5.0/docs/api/java/lang/System.html#exit(int)\">System.exit()</a> call for more info...</p>','<p>If you are java programmer or reading lots of books about java , you always see something in first chapters that there must be at least one main method for a java application to run or at least jvm know where to start to run the application. Here is a little java hack that prints the hello world string without using main method instead using static initialization block and than print the string to the console , try to run from command line cause eclipse would not allow you to run the application cause it doesnt hava main method.\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1269997.js?file=static_main\"></script>\n<p>Probably after running and loading the class you get an error saying that i can not find the main method to run, you can bypass this error by providing System.exit(0) to inform the compiler , on background System.exit is calling</p>\n<blockquote>Runtime.getRuntime().exit(n)</blockquote>\n<p>and than it should work and succesfully run the application.</p>\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1269998.js?file=static_main2\"></script>\n<p>You should check static <a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/javaOO/initial.html\">initialization</a> if you are wondering the answer and also look at <a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/javase/1.5.0/docs/api/java/lang/System.html#exit(int)\">System.exit()</a> call for more info...</p>','2011-10-05 23:34:32','2011-10-07 10:39:41'),(12,1,'search-for-answer-as-developer','Search For Answer As Developer','<p>Searching something on the web is a long time consuming process especially if you are developing software in a different area you dont have too much experience before , it is needed if you dealing with some kind of issue or a problem that you expect to find and learn how to implement.I am going to talk over \"Android\" example cause lets say i am searching a lot about android these days.  Lets say you are creating an listview with Android but in a customized way. You learn how listview works how it is rendered by Android UI and after you get the basics of it , you design your customized listview and directly dive into problem to create custom listview (lets be honest without knowing the basics and diving directly into problem tackles your process a lot while developing software at least me work in this way , some people prefer this way but i am not that kind of people) . You did what you learn from the basics of listview and implemented the your custom listview , but it is not working the way you expected , lets define the steps that can be follow after facing with similar situation.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>1- First try to understand the problem</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Not understanding problem and trying to search something that you dont get is just a waste of time.Yes there is a problem in listview but what it is ? Is listview not showing data correctly or data is fine but something wrong with the view of the list ? If data is not shown correctly there may be problem with you data :) simple isnt it no need to search for other places just check if your data is correct or related methods with it. Lets say our problem with the view of the list and data not directly data itself.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>2- Try to recover from problem yourself</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Aftet getting the problem what it is try to find a solution by yourself not directly diving into lots of web pages related to topic or forums that have ugly user interface or at worst not finding direct answer and after asking a problem waiting for a solution to come from someone else. Also this approach make you give up about the problems so easily , if you can not find similar problem that other people face after searching you gave up and say \"this cant be done , lets try different way\" , may be there is a way but you didnt try hard enough to implement or find it. Lets get back to problem , try to focus on the problem description if you have one , if not try to debug your code carefully or try to analyze log info about software (if logging comes default add your specific logs about software there is a approach i saw these days <strong><a href=\"http://thedailywtf.com/Articles/Log-Everything.aspx\">@DailtWTF</a></strong> \"Log everything\" but i dont think just logging everything solves your problem but at least look at it ,its different ) generally this step leads you to the solution but sometimes you can not find the solution with just debugging the code.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>3- There is a web search , lets try it out </strong></h3>\r\n<p>Yes next thing you probably try to search the problem , first try to find the \"<em>exact match</em>\" with your problem if you find the exact match with your problem you are lucky ,just apply the same thing to your code this will do the job for you.How to find the exact match with your problem needs some experience about serching google ,yeah you heard it right <a href=\"http://prezi.com/mohshuoe-qcf/google-search-tricks/\">expertise searching sth on google</a> if not you see similar situation <a href=\"http://lmgtfy.com/?q=use+the+right+words\">like this</a> . Second try to find \"<em>close match</em>\" to your problem your are dealing with not directly use sentence (actually <a href=\"http://www.google.com/instant/\">serch industry evolve</a> a lot so you can use that approach too) instead use keywords that valuable for that problem , in our situation keywords are \"listview\" \"android\" \"adapter\" \"custom\" \"view\" \"show\" try the combination of this keywords for your needs. After you find similar problem try to save your last working state if you dont want to make things lot harder with mixing your existing problem with new one (saving last working step is just an approach i am doing to not lose time while returning working state).</p>\r\n<h3><strong>4- Still not working ??? </strong></h3>\r\n<p>You do all still not working ? may be you have to check your implementation again high probably you miss someting in your code like <a href=\"http://stackoverflow.com/questions/4480071/listview-does-not-show-custom-arrayadapter-correctly\">i did here</a> , if you miss something or implement it wrongly conguratulations you loose probably your 3 valuable hour with searching for a problem that you cause , the solution is simple you are probably programmer just sleep well :) If you have a different search process share it on your comment so that we can learn</p>','<p>Searching something on the web is a long time consuming process especially if you are developing software in a different area you dont have too much experience before , it is needed if you dealing with some kind of issue or a problem that you expect to find and learn how to implement.I am going to talk over \"Android\" example cause lets say i am searching a lot about android these days.  Lets say you are creating an listview with Android but in a customized way. You learn how listview works how it is rendered by Android UI and after you get the basics of it , you design your customized listview and directly dive into problem to create custom listview (lets be honest without knowing the basics and diving directly into problem tackles your process a lot while developing software at least me work in this way , some people prefer this way but i am not that kind of people) . You did what you learn from the basics of listview and implemented the your custom listview , but it is not working the way you expected , lets define the steps that can be follow after facing with similar situation.</p>\n\n<h3><strong>1- First try to understand the problem</strong></h3>\n\n<p>Not understanding problem and trying to search something that you dont get is just a waste of time.Yes there is a problem in listview but what it is ? Is listview not showing data correctly or data is fine but something wrong with the view of the list ? If data is not shown correctly there may be problem with you data :) simple isnt it no need to search for other places just check if your data is correct or related methods with it. Lets say our problem with the view of the list and data not directly data itself.</p>\n\n<h3><strong>2- Try to recover from problem yourself</strong></h3>\n\n<p>Aftet getting the problem what it is try to find a solution by yourself not directly diving into lots of web pages related to topic or forums that have ugly user interface or at worst not finding direct answer and after asking a problem waiting for a solution to come from someone else. Also this approach make you give up about the problems so easily , if you can not find similar problem that other people face after searching you gave up and say \"this cant be done , lets try different way\" , may be there is a way but you didnt try hard enough to implement or find it. Lets get back to problem , try to focus on the problem description if you have one , if not try to debug your code carefully or try to analyze log info about software (if logging comes default add your specific logs about software there is a approach i saw these days <strong><a href=\"http://thedailywtf.com/Articles/Log-Everything.aspx\">@DailtWTF</a></strong> \"Log everything\" but i dont think just logging everything solves your problem but at least look at it ,its different ) generally this step leads you to the solution but sometimes you can not find the solution with just debugging the code.</p>\n\n<h3><strong>3- There is a web search , lets try it out </strong></h3>\n\n<p>Yes next thing you probably try to search the problem , first try to find the \"<em>exact match</em>\" with your problem if you find the exact match with your problem you are lucky ,just apply the same thing to your code this will do the job for you.How to find the exact match with your problem needs some experience about serching google ,yeah you heard it right <a href=\"http://prezi.com/mohshuoe-qcf/google-search-tricks/\">expertise searching sth on google</a> if not you see similar situation <a href=\"http://lmgtfy.com/?q=use+the+right+words\">like this</a> . Second try to find \"<em>close match</em>\" to your problem your are dealing with not directly use sentence (actually <a href=\"http://www.google.com/instant/\">serch industry evolve</a> a lot so you can use that approach too) instead use keywords that valuable for that problem , in our situation keywords are \"listview\" \"android\" \"adapter\" \"custom\" \"view\" \"show\" try the combination of this keywords for your needs. After you find similar problem try to save your last working state if you dont want to make things lot harder with mixing your existing problem with new one (saving last working step is just an approach i am doing to not lose time while returning working state).</p>\n\n<h3><strong>4- Still not working ??? </strong></h3>\n\n<p>You do all still not working ? may be you have to check your implementation again high probably you miss someting in your code like <a href=\"http://stackoverflow.com/questions/4480071/listview-does-not-show-custom-arrayadapter-correctly\">i did here</a> , if you miss something or implement it wrongly conguratulations you loose probably your 3 valuable hour with searching for a problem that you cause , the solution is simple you are probably programmer just sleep well :) If you have a different search process share it on your comment so that we can learn</p>','2011-10-05 23:35:45','2011-10-05 23:35:45'),(13,1,'creating-custom-listview-in-android-application','Creating Custom ListView in Android Application','<p><img class=\"posterous_download_image\" title=\"Simple Listview With Image\" src=\"/static/images/uploads/listview.png\" align=left alt=\"\" width=\"347\" height=\"503\" />Listview is one of the most common widget that is used android applications if you especially showing lots of data from web service or database or from similar resource.</p>\r\n<blockquote>A view that shows items in a vertically scrolling list. The items come from the ListAdapter associated with this view.</blockquote>\r\n<p>Thats whats <a href=\"http://developer.android.com/reference/android/widget/ListView.html\">android developer documentation</a> says about ListView , yes its basicly show items in scrollable environment and also list items comes from default adapter or adapter that is created custom for Listview.  Lets first create our listview and than we can create an adapter to fill some string in it to show more appealing way.  First lets create a new project to do all these stuff. I am going to name it <em><strong>CustomListView</strong></em> gave sdk version as <strong><em>2.3</em></strong> (latest version which min sdk version 9) and create activity called <strong><em>ListViewActivity</em></strong>.Here is ListViewActivity at first. It is not doing something special right now just getting the main xml as a layout setting it and waiting idle. What is on our mind that we must put an listview in that main layout then creating an custom adapter and finally putting some sort of data in it and show it. Thats our route to create our listview. First lets look at how listview looks like with some data in it. <a href=\"http://developer.android.com/resources/articles/images/list_fade_1.png\">Here</a> is a image of it</p>\r\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1269964.js\"> Simple Code </script>\r\n<p>We basicly do most of our job at <strong><em>onCreate</em></strong> method. Then i modify main.xml which reside in <strong><em>res/layout</em></strong> directory you can change name if you want but i will stick with default one. I am gonna add listview to <strong><em>main.xml</em></strong> and fill with some hardcoded values than i am going to use adapter to fill listview.Here is my main.xml file.</p>\r\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1269974.js?file=main.xml\"></script>\r\n<p>We just added listview object to xml file with id <em>myListView </em>and width and height, you can give fancy stuff here color,orientation etc. I am using <em><strong>LinearLayout</strong></em> you can use whatever you want.Than we are going to create one more xml , we will use that xml while drawing rows of the listview with our adapter. Lets name it <strong><em>rows.xml</em></strong> and put one imageview and textview inside , we place the imageview left of the textview like a bullet and give our dummy data to textview.</p>\r\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1269978.js?file=rows.xml\"></script>\r\n<p>As you can see i put one <em>imageview</em> and <strong><em>textview</em></strong> , it is best practice to give id\'s to widgets in xml especially clear names which show their intents , one more important thing here i gave <em><strong>android:src</strong></em> attiribure which shows where the imageview source image is , you must place image inside any of the directory under the res/drawable-***, drawable-hdpi means high resolution images , mdpi means medium resolution and ldpi means low resolution , i put inside the mdpi directory.Another important thing here is <strong><em>android:layout_toRightof</em></strong> attribute meaning put this widget to right of the given widget with its id.</p>\r\n<blockquote>Another best practice is that you must define text like resource in unit of <strong>sp</strong> on the other hand define margin,padding height,width like attributes in the unit of <strong>dip</strong> . You can look at android developer site what these unit means and their advantages.</blockquote>\r\n<p>Now we have our main view and listview row view lets create our adapter and put some dummy data in it. In order to create adapter you have to extend ArrayAdapter class and at least implement some of its methods like getView to draw our data.Here is our custom adapter.</p>\r\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1269985.js?file=MyArrayAdapter\"></script>\r\n<p>I put comment you can check if you wanna understand parts of the methods and other stuff. But basically we are extending ArrayAdapter class and implementing one of its constructors , in constructor i am getting the list of object and context then getView method inflate our rows.xml and at last putting some data inside textview of the every row. As i said lets create some dummy data , here is my dummy data\'s and dummy method to do it.</p>\r\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1269986.js?file=dummy\"></script>\r\n<p>We fill out some data in it . Next step would be setting our custom array adapter to listview by calling setAdapter method on listview object before that you have to get the listview object either by calling findViewById method or if you are extending ListActivity by calling getListView method.</p>\r\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1269987.js?file=findViewById\"></script>\r\n<p>Listview is very customizable widget you can do different things with it , important thing in here to learn how android handle getView method internally , how it is drawing listview rows is it reusing objects or not these things important not the code itself cause while developing applications you will face with weird behaviours like your data wouldnt shown on the list or scroll does not function properly to solve these issues you must understand how android handles these with that knowladge you can easily spot the problematic area and fix it.I am going to put the<a href=\"http://dl.dropbox.com/u/7829209/Thrash/CustomListView.zip\"> full source code here</a> you can check source as a hole to understand more.</p>','<p><img class=\"posterous_download_image\" title=\"Simple Listview With Image\" src=\"/static/images/uploads/listview.png\" align=left alt=\"\" width=\"347\" height=\"503\" />Listview is one of the most common widget that is used android applications if you especially showing lots of data from web service or database or from similar resource.</p>\n\n<blockquote>A view that shows items in a vertically scrolling list. The items come from the ListAdapter associated with this view.</blockquote>\n\n<p>Thats whats <a href=\"http://developer.android.com/reference/android/widget/ListView.html\">android developer documentation</a> says about ListView , yes its basicly show items in scrollable environment and also list items comes from default adapter or adapter that is created custom for Listview.  Lets first create our listview and than we can create an adapter to fill some string in it to show more appealing way.  First lets create a new project to do all these stuff. I am going to name it <em><strong>CustomListView</strong></em> gave sdk version as <strong><em>2.3</em></strong> (latest version which min sdk version 9) and create activity called <strong><em>ListViewActivity</em></strong>.Here is ListViewActivity at first. It is not doing something special right now just getting the main xml as a layout setting it and waiting idle. What is on our mind that we must put an listview in that main layout then creating an custom adapter and finally putting some sort of data in it and show it. Thats our route to create our listview. First lets look at how listview looks like with some data in it. <a href=\"http://developer.android.com/resources/articles/images/list_fade_1.png\">Here</a> is a image of it</p>\n\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1269964.js\"> Simple Code </script>\n\n<p>We basicly do most of our job at <strong><em>onCreate</em></strong> method. Then i modify main.xml which reside in <strong><em>res/layout</em></strong> directory you can change name if you want but i will stick with default one. I am gonna add listview to <strong><em>main.xml</em></strong> and fill with some hardcoded values than i am going to use adapter to fill listview.Here is my main.xml file.</p>\n\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1269974.js?file=main.xml\"></script>\n\n<p>We just added listview object to xml file with id <em>myListView </em>and width and height, you can give fancy stuff here color,orientation etc. I am using <em><strong>LinearLayout</strong></em> you can use whatever you want.Than we are going to create one more xml , we will use that xml while drawing rows of the listview with our adapter. Lets name it <strong><em>rows.xml</em></strong> and put one imageview and textview inside , we place the imageview left of the textview like a bullet and give our dummy data to textview.</p>\n\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1269978.js?file=rows.xml\"></script>\n\n<p>As you can see i put one <em>imageview</em> and <strong><em>textview</em></strong> , it is best practice to give id\'s to widgets in xml especially clear names which show their intents , one more important thing here i gave <em><strong>android:src</strong></em> attiribure which shows where the imageview source image is , you must place image inside any of the directory under the res/drawable-***, drawable-hdpi means high resolution images , mdpi means medium resolution and ldpi means low resolution , i put inside the mdpi directory.Another important thing here is <strong><em>android:layout_toRightof</em></strong> attribute meaning put this widget to right of the given widget with its id.</p>\n\n<blockquote>Another best practice is that you must define text like resource in unit of <strong>sp</strong> on the other hand define margin,padding height,width like attributes in the unit of <strong>dip</strong> . You can look at android developer site what these unit means and their advantages.</blockquote>\n\n<p>Now we have our main view and listview row view lets create our adapter and put some dummy data in it. In order to create adapter you have to extend ArrayAdapter class and at least implement some of its methods like getView to draw our data.Here is our custom adapter.</p>\n\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1269985.js?file=MyArrayAdapter\"></script>\n\n<p>I put comment you can check if you wanna understand parts of the methods and other stuff. But basically we are extending ArrayAdapter class and implementing one of its constructors , in constructor i am getting the list of object and context then getView method inflate our rows.xml and at last putting some data inside textview of the every row. As i said lets create some dummy data , here is my dummy data\'s and dummy method to do it.</p>\n\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1269986.js?file=dummy\"></script>\n\n<p>We fill out some data in it . Next step would be setting our custom array adapter to listview by calling setAdapter method on listview object before that you have to get the listview object either by calling findViewById method or if you are extending ListActivity by calling getListView method.</p>\n\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1269987.js?file=findViewById\"></script>\n\n<p>Listview is very customizable widget you can do different things with it , important thing in here to learn how android handle getView method internally , how it is drawing listview rows is it reusing objects or not these things important not the code itself cause while developing applications you will face with weird behaviours like your data wouldnt shown on the list or scroll does not function properly to solve these issues you must understand how android handles these with that knowladge you can easily spot the problematic area and fix it.I am going to put the<a href=\"http://dl.dropbox.com/u/7829209/Thrash/CustomListView.zip\"> full source code here</a> you can check source as a hole to understand more.</p>','2011-10-05 23:37:11','2011-10-07 10:37:59'),(14,1,'endless-scroll-effect-with-android','ENDLESS SCROLL EFFECT WITH ANDROID','Endless scroll effect gives you ability to show items with nice transition if you have lots of items especially if you are using listview. Endless scroll effect can also be suitable for making post and get connections. Lets try to implement this transition this is not built into Android SDK i try to implement this behaviour with source code given below.\r\n\r\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270016.js?file=EndlessScrollActivity\"></script>\r\n\r\nWe have to implement onScrollListener in order to implement endless scroll effect than do all the logic inside the onScroll method of the activity. Lets say we have 30 item in list and every http request get 30 more item , we better create variable named \"visibleThreshold\"  this variable will be used to check if we reach end of the list ,if we are close the end of the list we will do another http request ( or what you wanna do ). Lets say it is 3 , when we reach last 3 of the item from end of the list we will automatically make another request to get 30 item more and notify adapter that new items will show up.\r\n\r\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270020.js?file=gistfile1.txt\"></script>\r\n\r\npreviousTotal hold the total item in the list previously and loading is a boolean value to check if at that moment we are loading data from network. Now lets see onScroll method how to implement endless scroll effect.\r\n\r\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270025.js?file=gistfile1.java\"></script>\r\n\r\nHere the main logic that implements endless scroll effect in the list , i often do this job in the AsyncTask\'s doinBackground method and to warn the user i show a little pop up informing that more data is on the way. Here is the dialog code.\r\n\r\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270027.js?file=gistfile1.java\"></script>\r\n\r\nLets say we do all the networking in AsynchTask actually this is best practice to do the network or similar jobs at background i am not go into details of the AsynchTask right now but i will give the generic code to complete subject.\r\n\r\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270028.js?file=gistfile1.java\"></script>\r\n\r\nAsynchTask is very easy comparing to other Thread environments just do the preparing stuff in onPreExecute , do the main job and doInBackground method , after thread is completed do what you wanna do at onPostExecute. Check the code above for better understanding. But important thing to consider you can not change main thread(which draw the main interface widgets) from background thread above onPreExecute and onPostExecute are main thread methods except doInBackground its a background thread method so \"do not change interface from background thread\".','<p>Endless scroll effect gives you ability to show items with nice transition if you have lots of items especially if you are using listview. Endless scroll effect can also be suitable for making post and get connections. Lets try to implement this transition this is not built into Android SDK i try to implement this behaviour with source code given below.</p>\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270016.js?file=EndlessScrollActivity\"></script>\n\n<p>We have to implement onScrollListener in order to implement endless scroll effect than do all the logic inside the onScroll method of the activity. Lets say we have 30 item in list and every http request get 30 more item , we better create variable named \"visibleThreshold\"  this variable will be used to check if we reach end of the list ,if we are close the end of the list we will do another http request ( or what you wanna do ). Lets say it is 3 , when we reach last 3 of the item from end of the list we will automatically make another request to get 30 item more and notify adapter that new items will show up.</p>\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270020.js?file=gistfile1.txt\"></script>\n\n<p>previousTotal hold the total item in the list previously and loading is a boolean value to check if at that moment we are loading data from network. Now lets see onScroll method how to implement endless scroll effect.</p>\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270025.js?file=gistfile1.java\"></script>\n\n<p>Here the main logic that implements endless scroll effect in the list , i often do this job in the AsyncTask\'s doinBackground method and to warn the user i show a little pop up informing that more data is on the way. Here is the dialog code.</p>\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270027.js?file=gistfile1.java\"></script>\n\n<p>Lets say we do all the networking in AsynchTask actually this is best practice to do the network or similar jobs at background i am not go into details of the AsynchTask right now but i will give the generic code to complete subject.</p>\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270028.js?file=gistfile1.java\"></script>\n\n<p>AsynchTask is very easy comparing to other Thread environments just do the preparing stuff in onPreExecute , do the main job and doInBackground method , after thread is completed do what you wanna do at onPostExecute. Check the code above for better understanding. But important thing to consider you can not change main thread(which draw the main interface widgets) from background thread above onPreExecute and onPostExecute are main thread methods except doInBackground its a background thread method so \"do not change interface from background thread\".</p>','2011-10-07 10:54:04','2011-10-07 10:54:04'),(15,1,'remove-underline-from-links-in-textview','REMOVE UNDERLINE FROM LINKS IN TEXTVIEW','I have mention about linkifying text in android textview widget , you can go check it again its here. But this time i will told you about removing underline from links that we use with linkify object cause default behaviour of the linkify is putting underline to links sometimes thats not the case we want and makes user interface ugly if you use it too much. Lets say you created some reguler expression to catch some pattern in your text but you wanna make them have no underline here is what you will do , you have to get the span array of the text object first then we will modify source of the android a little in order to links in the text have no underline. First we have to create some private class which extend URLSpan class and tell them to have no underline.Here is code.\r\n\r\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270040.js?file=NoSpan.java\"></script>\r\n\r\nAbove we create a class called URLSpanNoUnderline and extend it with the URLSpan class then in the updateDrawState method of that class we made textpain object to have no underline by setting ds.setUnderLineText(false). Now lets get our URLSpan array from our text object , remove previous span object and set new span to our newly created class above. Here is the code for that.\r\n\r\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270045.js?file=span_remove.java\"></script>\r\n\r\nNow we get our urlspan object , you can ask here what is entrySpan here its a spannable text that we can get from textview object easily with below code.\r\n\r\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270048.js?file=span.java\"></script>\r\n\r\nThats it now our links reside in the texts have no underline in order for your view to have different style like this you can always look at the source and modify a little bit and you are done thats the beauty of Android being open source environment.','<p>I have mention about linkifying text in android textview widget , you can go check it again its here. But this time i will told you about removing underline from links that we use with linkify object cause default behaviour of the linkify is putting underline to links sometimes thats not the case we want and makes user interface ugly if you use it too much. Lets say you created some reguler expression to catch some pattern in your text but you wanna make them have no underline here is what you will do , you have to get the span array of the text object first then we will modify source of the android a little in order to links in the text have no underline. First we have to create some private class which extend URLSpan class and tell them to have no underline.Here is code.</p>\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270040.js?file=NoSpan.java\"></script>\n\n<p>Above we create a class called URLSpanNoUnderline and extend it with the URLSpan class then in the updateDrawState method of that class we made textpain object to have no underline by setting ds.setUnderLineText(false). Now lets get our URLSpan array from our text object , remove previous span object and set new span to our newly created class above. Here is the code for that.</p>\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270045.js?file=span_remove.java\"></script>\n\n<p>Now we get our urlspan object , you can ask here what is entrySpan here its a spannable text that we can get from textview object easily with below code.</p>\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270048.js?file=span.java\"></script>\n\n<p>Thats it now our links reside in the texts have no underline in order for your view to have different style like this you can always look at the source and modify a little bit and you are done thats the beauty of Android being open source environment.</p>','2011-10-07 10:59:30','2011-10-07 10:59:30'),(16,1,'how-linkify-your-text-in-android','HOW LINKIFY YOUR TEXT IN ANDROID','Linkify is one of the good features of the Android SDK which gives you flexibility to turn any group of text into link. Of course you can turn actual web links to web urls thats not to hard but what if you have pattern in your text you wanna make link and also these links call another activity in your application instead of web browser as normal web links do. First lets dig into how to transform your text into actual web urls in the text and linkify them , actually thats easy you get the text which android can search for web urls and just linkify them here is a code that will do the job for you.\r\n\r\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270055.js?file=link.java\"></script>\r\n\r\nWe are getting the textview object and than creating links according to parameters given to linkify in this case Linkify.WEB_URLS which means that any string that matches with the url pattern. Then i set the link color of the text with preferred one this time with #FFF hex color. Now as a next step lets turn any phone number into actual phone number link so that when user click these phone number links they can call these numbers. Here is a sample code for this.\r\n\r\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270062.js?file=phone.java\"></script>\r\n\r\nNow when user click one of the phone links phone try to call these numbers automatically. Lets choose another case this time you wanna make email adresses as a link. This is no different from other examples just change the Linkify mask into EMAIL_ADRESSES than test if mail app automatically call by your application , Here is a sample code.\r\n\r\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270064.js?file=email.java\"></script>\r\n\r\nThese are not hard examples and most used ones . But how about a text that include a pattern you wanna linkify , how can you achieve this ? Lets say you are developing a twitter client application and you wanna linkify @username field in the twit text and you wanna call your app activity when user click these links. This could be hard ata first look. But it is not as hard as you think . If you have a little experience on regular expression this makes your life easier in this situation or similar ones. First you have to give pattern to catch @username in the text , then you have to define intent filter in order to catch when user click these links and then give all of them to linkify it will make everything work. Lets look at some sample code.\r\n\r\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270066.js?file=regex.java\"></script>\r\n\r\nPattern is used to create new pattern from given reguler expression like example above which catch any text like @username in the given text , then you have to define your user:// scheme this also have to be defined in activity which will catch the clicks and last one Linkify.addLinks make all of them work together. Lets look at Android.manifest file for intent filter.\r\n\r\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270068.js?file=filter.xml\"></script>\r\n\r\nWhen you click @username this is the activity that will catch the click and process the clicked string. Yes we didnt mention about what is send to DirectMessageActivity when user click @username , as you might guess \"username\" string will be passed to DirectMessageActivity. You can get this string like this.\r\n\r\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270070.js?file=data.java\"></script>\r\n\r\nThis is how you can make links using some pattern along with the reguler expression and attach these links to your app activities.','<p>Linkify is one of the good features of the Android SDK which gives you flexibility to turn any group of text into link. Of course you can turn actual web links to web urls thats not to hard but what if you have pattern in your text you wanna make link and also these links call another activity in your application instead of web browser as normal web links do. First lets dig into how to transform your text into actual web urls in the text and linkify them , actually thats easy you get the text which android can search for web urls and just linkify them here is a code that will do the job for you.</p>\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270055.js?file=link.java\"></script>\n\n<p>We are getting the textview object and than creating links according to parameters given to linkify in this case Linkify.WEB_URLS which means that any string that matches with the url pattern. Then i set the link color of the text with preferred one this time with #FFF hex color. Now as a next step lets turn any phone number into actual phone number link so that when user click these phone number links they can call these numbers. Here is a sample code for this.</p>\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270062.js?file=phone.java\"></script>\n\n<p>Now when user click one of the phone links phone try to call these numbers automatically. Lets choose another case this time you wanna make email adresses as a link. This is no different from other examples just change the Linkify mask into EMAIL_ADRESSES than test if mail app automatically call by your application , Here is a sample code.</p>\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270064.js?file=email.java\"></script>\n\n<p>These are not hard examples and most used ones . But how about a text that include a pattern you wanna linkify , how can you achieve this ? Lets say you are developing a twitter client application and you wanna linkify @username field in the twit text and you wanna call your app activity when user click these links. This could be hard ata first look. But it is not as hard as you think . If you have a little experience on regular expression this makes your life easier in this situation or similar ones. First you have to give pattern to catch @username in the text , then you have to define intent filter in order to catch when user click these links and then give all of them to linkify it will make everything work. Lets look at some sample code.</p>\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270066.js?file=regex.java\"></script>\n\n<p>Pattern is used to create new pattern from given reguler expression like example above which catch any text like @username in the given text , then you have to define your user:// scheme this also have to be defined in activity which will catch the clicks and last one Linkify.addLinks make all of them work together. Lets look at Android.manifest file for intent filter.</p>\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270068.js?file=filter.xml\"></script>\n\n<p>When you click @username this is the activity that will catch the click and process the clicked string. Yes we didnt mention about what is send to DirectMessageActivity when user click @username , as you might guess \"username\" string will be passed to DirectMessageActivity. You can get this string like this.</p>\n<script src=\"https://gist.github.com/1270070.js?file=data.java\"></script>\n\n<p>This is how you can make links using some pattern along with the reguler expression and attach these links to your app activities.</p>','2011-10-07 11:05:09','2011-10-07 11:05:09'),(17,1,'bu-yaz-ne-yapiyosun-ne-yapiyorum','BU YAZ NE YAPIYOSUN, NE YAPIYORUM ?','<p><img src=\"/static/images/uploads/sonisphere.jpg\" align=left/>Evet bu sorunun cevabÄ±nÄ± hen&uuml;z bende bilmiyorum ancak bu yaz hi&ccedil; olmadÄ±ÄÄ±m kadar bana ayrÄ±lmÄ±Å bir yaz olacaÄÄ±nÄ± tahmin ediyorum.Okul,iÅ,staj derken yaklaÅÄ±k 2&nbsp;senedir hi&ccedil;bir yaz tam anlamÄ±yla bana ait olmadÄ±, bu yaz bana ait derken bir tarafÄ±mÄ± yayÄ±p tatil yerlinden &ccedil;ektiÄim fotoÄraflarÄ± twitter\'a facebook\'a g&ouml;nderecek bir yaz tatilide beklenmesin benden bizimki az, &ouml;z ve sessiz oluyo ger&ccedil;i bekleneceÄinide sanmÄ±yorum zaten.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Staj vb iÅlere girmedim &ccedil;&uuml;nk&uuml; yeterince o tecr&uuml;beyi doya doya tattÄ±ÄÄ±mÄ± <a href=\"http://www.turkcell.com.tr/turkcellhakkinda/insankaynaklari/turkcelldekariyer/profesyonelgelisimdanismanligi\">d&uuml;Å&uuml;n&uuml;yorum</a>. Ger&ccedil;i 2 sene gibi uzun bir s&uuml;re oldu staj biteli ancak devamÄ±nda gelen iÅ tecr&uuml;besi staj yapmayÄ± gereksiz kÄ±ldÄ±. Tekrardan staja baÅvurmak demek tekrardan yeni bir firma k&uuml;lt&uuml;r&uuml;ne ayak uydurmak, s&uuml;re&ccedil;lerini &ouml;Ärenmek demektir ki T&uuml;rkiyede 3 aylÄ±k s&uuml;re altÄ±nda staj yapÄ±lan hi&ccedil;bir yerde verimli olarak s&uuml;re&ccedil;lerin anlaÅÄ±labildiÄini ve anlaÅÄ±lacaÄÄ±nÄ± d&uuml;Å&uuml;nm&uuml;yorum. Bu 2 sene boyunca bir&ccedil;ok konuya el attÄ±m ve i&ccedil;ine daldÄ±m, kimi zaman debelendim kimi zaman rahatlÄ±kla yaptÄ±m ancak geriye baktÄ±ÄÄ±mda hÄ±zlÄ± bir geliÅme kaydettiÄimi s&ouml;yleyebilirim &ouml;zellikle okul ve iÅ cidden yanyana iyi ge&ccedil;inen bir ikili deÄil eÄer becermeyi bilmiyorsanÄ±z.</p>\r\n<p>Staj yerine full zamanlÄ± da &ccedil;alÄ±Åabilirdim ancak bunu da tercih etmiyorum artÄ±k, &ccedil;&uuml;nk&uuml; bundan bir sene sonra kendi istediÄim Åeylerle uÄraÅabileceÄimden kesin emin olamadÄ±ÄÄ±m (ne kadar bu konuda rahat olabileceÄim d&uuml;zeye ve konuma g&ouml;re kendimi hazÄ±rlasam da) i&ccedil;in bu kÄ±sÄ±tlÄ± zamanlarda kendi yapmak istediÄim ve uzun s&uuml;redir ertelediÄim Åeyleri yapmayÄ± d&uuml;Å&uuml;n&uuml;yorum hem sosyal hem teknik anlamda. A&ccedil;Ä±k&ccedil;asÄ± bir konu bana ilgi &ccedil;ekici gelmiyorsa pek de &uuml;zerine d&uuml;Å&uuml;p uÄraÅmayÄ± seven biri deÄilim her konuda bu b&ouml;yle. O y&uuml;zden 3 aylÄ±k dilimde uÄraÅmayÄ± d&uuml;Å&uuml;nd&uuml;Ä&uuml;m bir&ccedil;ok madde var ancak bunlarÄ±n hepsine ayrÄ± ayrÄ± dalarak da ziyan etmek istemiyorum &ccedil;&uuml;nk&uuml; daha &ouml;nce baÅÄ±ma geldi bir&ccedil;ok Åeyi yapmaya &ccedil;alÄ±ÅÄ±rken arka arkaya hepsinden&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.burakdede.com/how-did-i-fail-from-my-microsoft-interview\">&ccedil;uvallamak gibi</a>. O y&uuml;zden bu konudan aÄzÄ±m yandÄ±ÄÄ± i&ccedil;in Åimdi daha temkinli davranÄ±yorum ne kadar &uuml;niversite projeleri bunu aksi y&ouml;nde bir program &ccedil;izsede yazÄ±n bunlar ortadan kalkÄ±cak.</p>\r\n<p>Son se&ccedil;enek olarak kendi merak ettiÄim bir konuda yepyeni bir dil,framework ya da teknoloji kullanarak ortaya bir &uuml;r&uuml;n &ccedil;Ä±karmak. Bu kesinlikle diÄer se&ccedil;enekler arasÄ±nda en kulaÄa hoÅ geleni ve evet diÄerlerine g&ouml;re kÄ±sa s&uuml;re&ccedil;te maddi bir getirisi yok ancak uzun s&uuml;re&ccedil;te getirisine bakarsan diÄerleri solda sÄ±fÄ±r kalÄ±r, s&uuml;per b&uuml;y&uuml;k bir Åirkette staj yapmÄ±Å gibi g&ouml;r&uuml;n&uuml;p aslÄ±nda hi&ccedil;bir Åey yapmayanlarÄ±, normal &ccedil;alÄ±ÅtÄ±ÄÄ± yerde hi&ccedil;bir Åey yapmadan mesai bitimini bekleyip yinede &ccedil;ok &ccedil;alÄ±ÅÄ±yormuÅ gibi g&ouml;r&uuml;n&uuml;nleride. Åimdi biraz kafa yorup nasÄ±l birÅey yapabileceÄimi d&uuml;Å&uuml;nelim</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>&ouml;ncelikle kesinlikle \"&ouml;yle birÅey yapmalÄ±yÄ±m ki herkes kullansÄ±n bende bundan ya zengin olurum ya da facebook google microsoft gibi Åirketlere satarÄ±m\" gibi bir g&ouml;r&uuml;Åle ortaya &ccedil;Ä±kmÄ±yoruz.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>ikincisi kimse sizin kÄ±&ccedil;Ä± kÄ±rÄ±k bir projeyi php,mysql,apache ile yapÄ±p i&ccedil;ine hi&ccedil;bir yeni teknoloji katmadÄ±ÄÄ±nÄ±z ya da ihtiya&ccedil;tan doÄan bir &uuml;r&uuml;n ortaya koymadÄ±ÄÄ±nÄ±z, sadece yapmÄ±Å olmak i&ccedil;in yaptÄ±ÄÄ±nÄ±z projeye kuruÅ vermez. Ihtiya&ccedil; olmasÄ±da zorunluluk deÄil sadece nasÄ±l sistemin nasÄ±l &ccedil;alÄ±ÅtÄ±ÄÄ±nÄ± &ouml;Ärenmek i&ccedil;in bile benzer bir proje kopyalanabilir. Ä°htiya&ccedil;tan neler yapÄ±labileceÄinin bir &ouml;rneÄini ben size <a href=\"http://developers.facebook.com/blog/post/358/\">Å&ouml;yle</a> vereyim gerisini siz araÅtÄ±rÄ±p zaten bulursunuz hadi bir tane daha vereyim i&ccedil;imde kalmasÄ±n <a href=\"http://cassandra.apache.org/\">facebook\'un bir kÄ±yaÄÄ±</a>. Ha bunlar zart diye karÅÄ±mÄ±za sÄ±fÄ±r ve &ccedil;alÄ±ÅÄ±r halde gelen projeler mi hayÄ±r bildiÄim kadarÄ±yla hiphop 2 senelik bir geliÅtirme &uuml;r&uuml;n&uuml; keza cassandra\'da top level apache projesi olmadan &ouml;nce apache incubator altÄ±ndaydÄ±. Gidip araÅtÄ±rÄ±rsanÄ±z satÄ±n alÄ±mlarda genelde ya arkada cidden g&uuml;zel bir fikir vardÄ±r ve ortaya d&uuml;zg&uuml;n bir sunumla konulmuÅtur ya da arkada bir beyin transferi yapÄ±lmak istenmiÅtir genelde b&ouml;yledir ama istisnalarÄ±da mevcuttur tabii ki bu konuda &ccedil;ok da uzman olmadÄ±ÄÄ±m i&ccedil;in daha fazlada sallamak fikir sallamak istemiyorum sadece g&ouml;rd&uuml;klerimi s&ouml;yl&uuml;yorum.</li>\r\n<li>daha &ouml;nceden tecr&uuml;be ettiÄiniz bir konuda yola &ccedil;Ä±kmak her zaman iyi bir &ccedil;&ouml;z&uuml;m ve zaman kazandÄ±rÄ±cÄ± olacaktÄ±r. &Ouml;rneÄin okul projesi olarak senkronizasyon ile ilgili bir network uygulamasÄ± mÄ± yazdÄ±nÄ±z bu sizin bu konuda belli bir seviyeye geldiÄinizi g&ouml;sterir ve bundan devÅireceÄiniz projelerde size zaman kazandÄ±rÄ±r. &Ouml;rneÄin bu proje boyunca edindiÄiniz bilgiyi benzer bir uygulamayÄ± web &uuml;zerinde port ederek ve <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cloud_storage\">cloud storage</a> kullanarak ortaya &ccedil;Ä±karmak size b&uuml;y&uuml;k tecr&uuml;beler kazandÄ±rÄ±r hele de bu aralar <a href=\"http://t.co/Pbaetbj\">dropbox\'Ä±n suyu Ä±sÄ±nmÄ±Åken</a>. Ve sistemin kullanÄ±cÄ± tarafÄ±nda nerelerde eksiklerini olduÄunu ve sizin sisteminizde <a href=\"http://dereknewton.com/2011/04/dropbox-authentication-static-host-ids/\">bu a&ccedil;Ä±klarÄ±</a> nasÄ±l <a href=\"http://dereknewton.com/2011/04/forensic-artifacts-dropbox/\">kapatmanÄ±z</a> gerektiÄini bilerek. Bu konuda a&ccedil;Ä±k kaynak bir proje bulursanÄ±z ne ÅanslÄ±sÄ±nÄ±z, size b&uuml;y&uuml;k yol g&ouml;sterici olacaktÄ±r.</li>\r\n<li>gelelim ne gibi teknolojiler kullanacaÄÄ±nÄ±za ruby ve ruby on rails ikilisi son zamanlarda &ccedil;ok ilgili &ccedil;eken dil ve onun web &uuml;zerindeki framework\'&uuml; ve m&uuml;thiÅ bir community\'si var. Sadece <a href=\"http://corte.si/posts/code/devsurvey/index.html\">github istatistiklerini</a> bakarak bile ne kadar &ccedil;ok geliÅtiriciye sahip olduÄu hakkÄ±nda basit bir fikir edinebilirsiniz. Dil olarak ilk zamanlarda size biraz farklÄ± gelebilir ama eÄer java vb <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Type_system#Strong_and_weak_typing\">strong typed</a> dillerden gelen biriyseniz ruby programlarÄ±nÄ± yazmak sizin i&ccedil;in zevk olacaktÄ±r. Hele ruby &ouml;Ärendikten sonra ruby on rails ile web gelilÅtirmesi yapmak daha da zevkli kÄ±smÄ±. Kendine has <a href=\"http://stackoverflow.com/questions/503684/ruby-on-rails-scalability-performance\">scalability sorunlarÄ±</a> var ancak bu da iÅin tuzu biberi olacaktÄ±r ki bana g&ouml;re bu sorunlarla uÄraÅmak ve &ccedil;&ouml;z&uuml;m getirmek hepsinden daha &ouml;nemli bir tecr&uuml;be daha b&uuml;y&uuml;k sistemlerde &ccedil;alÄ±ÅtÄ±ÄÄ±nÄ±zda size kesinlikle yardÄ±mÄ± olacaktÄ±r.</li>\r\n<li>e birde mobil uygulama diye bir trend var, bu web uygulamanÄ±za ister platform bazlÄ± &ccedil;alÄ±Åarak ( android,iphone,blackberry) ya da <a href=\"http://www.phonegap.com/\">mobil bir framework</a> kullanarak tek uygulama ile b&uuml;t&uuml;n platformlarÄ± kapsamak diÄer bir &ccedil;&ouml;z&uuml;m a&ccedil;Ä±k&ccedil;asÄ± benim tercihim platform bazlÄ± &ccedil;alÄ±Åmak olur ancak tercihler <a href=\"http://martinfowler.com/bliki/CrossPlatformMobile.html\">zevke g&ouml;re deÄiÅebilir</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>ha bu arada hatÄ±rlatÄ±yÄ±m bunlarÄ± yaparken 3 ayÄ±nÄ±z gitti :( , hani tatil yapÄ±yoduk :) neyse <a href=\"http://web03.biletix.com/etkinlik/MLSON/TURKIYE/tr\">Åu konser</a> iyi gibi duruyo bende orda olacaÄÄ±m y&uuml;ksek ihitmal bizimde tatilimiz bu napalÄ±m, fotoÄrafta alakasÄ±z ama koyasÄ±m geldi sadece :)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<p><img src=\"/static/image